Trees¶

  • Traversals Method 1
  • Traversals Method 2
  • Traversals Method 3

Traverse Method 1¶

Draw a line (base) at bottom, draw line on left side of each node, and connect to base line

Draw a line (base) at bottom, draw in bottom middle of each node, and connect to base line

Draw a line (base) at bottom, draw line on right side of each node, and connect to base line

Traverse Method 2¶

Draw a line on left side of each node, then starting as root follow contour of each node

Draw a line on middle bottom of each node, then starting as root follow contour of each node

Draw a line on right side of each node, then starting as root follow contour of each node

Traverse Method 3¶

Use your finger pointing to right toward each node, then starting as root follow contour of each node.

Use your finger pointing upwards toward each node, then starting as root follow contour of each node.

Use your finger pointing to left towards each node, then starting as root follow contour of each node.
